               <p>WILLIAM MARKS. I was walking near <placeName id="t18260406-187-crimeloc999">St. Giles' church</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260406-187-crimeloc999" type="placeName" value="St. Giles' church"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260406-187-crimeloc999" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-187-off997 t18260406-187-crimeloc999"></join> on the 7th of March; I felt my right hand coat pocket fall down; I had a great many half-pence in it, and it was rather heavy; I turned round and saw the prisoner, who had pulled my handkerchief out; I ran after him; and he dropped it, and said "There is your handkerchief, but do not take me;" I took him back to the place, and some other person had picked it up.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. ROBERTS. Q. What time was this? A. A quarter-past seven o'clock, it was rather dark; I did not see any boys playing about; I saw the handkerchief in his hands, while I was running after him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-187-person1014">
                  THOMAS 
                  IRESON
               <interp inst="t18260406-187-person1014" type="surname" value="IRESON"></interp>
